this single star is for the food ONLY. it was some of the worst service I've ever had. we had waited 15 minutes before having to ask someone who our server was. we waited another 5 minutes for someone to come over. took another 10 minutes to get three bottled beers. we started with the nachos and deviled pickles which were ON POINT. our dinner orders were completely wrong but we ate it anyway instead of waiting 20 minutes for the right food. but what we did get was GREAT. we were done with food and another 30 minutes of tracking down our server to get checks. we had two checks for the table and for one of them we were brought someone else's closed check. so we took it as a sign that we didn't owe anything. saw our server sitting outside just hanging out with another table. we got asked for a manager and told her we weren't paying for the horrid experience we had. but let me be clear - the food was SO good. the right amount of spice in the nachos, wonderful bbq mac and delicious crab cake sandwich. probably best ordered to go but be sure to check that you get what you actually ordered.

I could say I love Ernst Cafe because of its charm, character and history, as well as the friendly courteous service and quality food and beverage. That is all most certainly true, but it's more than that for me. It is my past and now it is my legacy. I am thankful to my Grandparents, Edna and Malcolm Ernst for the opportunity. I am grateful to my many dear friends and customers throughout the years that have made Ernst Cafe a success story. And I am also proud to have built on and preserved the Ernst Cafe Legacy. The oldest continually operated business in The Historic Warehouse District. I am especially pleased and encouraged to have the fine people of Creole Cuisine and the Ammari family continue my family's legacy for many years to come.
